132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1284
S.P. 512 In Senate, March 25, 2025
An Act to Repeal Provisions of Law Governing the Privacy of
Broadband Internet Customer Personal Information
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator STEWART of Aroostook.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA c. 94, as amended, is repealed.
3 SUMMARY
44 This bill repeals the laws requiring providers of broadband Internet access service to
55 protect customer personal information from unauthorized use, disclosure or access and
66 prohibiting those providers from using, disclosing, selling or permitting access to customer
77 personal information without the express, affirmative consent of the customer.
